pr_title: Fix for the BlocksToolKit Bug Issue #2918
pr_body: Issue #2918 Reason: According to me after switching screen, reloadComponentPalette() function wasn't calling because it was inside the editor.isScreen1() check.

### About the Project:

Currently, the properties for the Screen1 form contains a number of project-wide properties such as App Name and Theme. We want these properties separated from the component and maintained on a separate dialog on the designer view.

### Solution Overview:

Three Sub Categories Added for grouping Project Properties, 
1. General
2. Theming
3. Publishing

### General Project Properties:
- AppName
- BlocksToolkit
- DefaultFileScope
- Icon
- ShowListAsJson
- Sizing
- TutorialURL

### Theming Project Properties:
- AccentColor
- PrimaryColor
- PrimaryColorDark
- Theme

### Publishing Project Properties:
- VersionCode
- VersionName

### Work Product:
![Final Dialog IMG](https://github.com/mit-cml/appinventor-sources/assets/61725413/102afb97-81b6-48d3-a643-f7adb83d83bf)


### Work Product Demo:
https://github.com/mit-cml/appinventor-sources/assets/61725413/2ccbe85b-951a-41b8-be61-52cb3ecb9b1c
